Vendored MMQ device kernels from llama.cpp
==========================================

Source: https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp
Pinned upstream commit: 5fd2dc2c41c342a75c26f9756ca6b1814ed05fb4
License: MIT (see below)

Vendored file(s):
  mmq.cuh   - copied verbatim from ggml/src/ggml-cuda/mmq.cuh with ONE surgical
              edit (marked "VENDOR EDIT (gemm/main)"): the two device kernels
              `mul_mat_q` and `mul_mat_q_stream_k_fixup` were changed from
              `static __global__` to `static __device__` so that stable-named
              extern "C" trampolines in ../mmq_kernels.cu can call them (a
              __global__ cannot be launched from another __global__). The
              `__launch_bounds__` qualifiers (illegal on a __device__ function)
              were moved to the trampolines.

The remaining MMQ headers (common.cuh, mma.cuh, vecdotq.cuh, ggml-common.h,
ggml.h, ...) are NOT copied; mmq_kernels.cu includes them directly from the
upstream tree via -I. The activation quantizer `quantize_mmq_q8_1` is copied
verbatim into mmq_kernels.cu (also MIT, same commit).

